race.description: Jeffs Joinery Memorial Country Boosted Bm58 Handicap
race.comment: WONDERFUL MISTAKE (11) improving filly desperate for this trip. Fourth-up today with the tongue-tie going and expect to see her a little closer in the run. The one to beat. THREEFOLD (13) going better than her current form suggests and can hold a forward position from the gate. Best figures hold up well in this easier contest. IMASTATEMENT (4) chasing her third straight victory after giving her rivals a galloping lesson at the last two runs. Expected to run the 1200m out from the awkward gate. CHICO CASINO (2) closed strongly on resumption with the 58.5kg to finish fourth over 1100m at Bathurst. Comes to hand quickly and capable of taking this out. OUR LITTLE STAR (7) covered plenty of ground in the run when fifth at Gundagai. Stalks the speed and stays in the calculations.
